Modular build script: Rework to support incremental builds

This introduces a build target graph, implemented in btarget.py.  The
description of NaCl's toolchain modules in build.py is now simpler and
more easily supports ad-hoc arrangements such as copying header files
into the newlib source tree.

btarget.py is the "trusted code base" as far as incrementality goes.
Changes to btarget.py will not necessarily trigger rebuilds, but
changes to build.py should.

Changes to the input source (binutils, gcc etc.) will not yet trigger
rebuilds, but changes to the build options (e.g. configure arguments)
will.

BUG=http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=484

